# SwiftFormat configuration for OFEM (OneLake Explorer for macOS)
# Tool: nicklockwood/SwiftFormat 0.61.1
# Swift version: 6.0 (all targets build in Swift 6 language mode — see project.yml)

--swiftversion 6.0

# Exclude generated, vendored, and build-artefact paths.
--exclude .build
--exclude DerivedData
--exclude Packages/OfemKit/.build
--exclude OneLake.xcodeproj

# Use sensible default rules. The only explicit rule changes below are
# the two cases where SwiftFormat's default would fight Swift 6 strict
# concurrency or produce unexpected churn on this codebase.

# redundantSelf: keep explicit `self.` inside closures — Swift 6 strict
# concurrency makes captures explicit; removing `self.` here would lose
# that clarity. Leave SwiftFormat's default (remove) but note if CI
# flags issues, add: --disable redundantSelf
